headline: Why Interactive Brokers (IBKR) Stock Is Falling Today
summary: Shares of electronic brokerage firm Interactive Brokers (NASDAQ:IBKR) fell 3.4% in the morning session after a technical pullback as the stock rallied on news of its upcoming inclusion in the S&P 500 index.

headline: Aegis Ventures Welcomes Healthcare Leaders John Driscoll and Cris Ross as Venture Partners
summary: Aegis Ventures today announced the appointment of two of healthcare's most accomplished executives – John Driscoll and Cris Ross – as Venture Partners. Aegis is a NYC-based venture studio that partners with entrepreneurs and health systems to launch and scale meaningful healthtech startups that drive healthcare forward.
